cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.DB 

The paper describes an information retrieval system that uses model-driven retrieval services to enhance the retrieval process. The services include co-word analysis, Bradfordizing, and author centrality, which are all relevant to the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The system also involves query expansion, which is commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and document ranking, which is relevant to both information retrieval and data mining (cs.DL). Additionally, the system may involve database management (cs.DB) to store and retrieve the documents. Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CL, and cs.DB.
